        "Tafsir by Ibn Kathir": "Ar-Raḥmān is more intensive in meaning than Ar-Raḥīm, but Ar-Raḥīm indicates the continuity and repetition of the action. He is perpetually merciful to His believing servants, His kindness never ceasing from them.",
        "Tafsir by At-Tabari": "Ar-Raḥīm: He is merciful to His believing servants, as He guided them to faith and provided them with steadfastness upon it.",
